  goal = "mos vcs commit currently writes commit objects unconditionally. Add a pre-commit gate that runs all harness rules with trigger = pre-commit before accepting the commit. If any harness fails, the commit is rejected with diagnostic output — analogous to K8s admission webhooks rejecting invalid resources before etcd write. This requires: (1) Add trigger field to harness blocks in rule artifacts (enum: manual, pre-commit, post-commit). (2) In mos vcs commit, collect all rules where harness.trigger = pre-commit, run them, and abort if any return non-zero. (3) Add --no-verify flag to mos vcs commit for escape hatch. The first built-in pre-commit harness should be mos lint, ensuring no governance schema violations are committed."
  kind = "feature"
  justifies = "NEED-2026-002"
